name: Total Expenditures Full-time instructional faculty
description: Total expenditures for full-time instructional faculty at the end of the fall term. (Include as full-time faculty all full-time employees who teach more than 50% of the time.)

name: Total Full-time instructional faculty
description: Total number of full-time instructional faculty at the end of the fall term. (Include as Full-time faculty all full-time employees who teach more than 50% of the time.)

name: Total Expenditures Part-time instructional faculty
description: Total expenditures for part-time instructional faculty and adjuncts.

name: Total Part-time instructional faculty
description: Total number of part-time instructional faculty at the end of the fall term.

name: Total Expenditures Other Full-time Employees
description: Total expenditures for other full-time employees. (Other full-time employees are administrators who perform one or more instructional activities as listed on Form 1B.)

name: Total Other Full-time Employees
description: Total number of other full-time employees.  (Other full-time employees are administrators who perform one or more instructional activities as listed on Form 1B.)

name: Salary and Benefits for Full-Time Faculty
description: Salary and benefits for Full-Time  Faculty at your institution that spend more than 50% of their time on credit instructional activities.

name: Number of Full-Time Instructional Faculty
description: Number of Full-Time  Instructional Faculty at the end of the fall term.

name: Number of Student Credit Hours Taught by Full-Time Instructional Faculty
description: Indicate the number of student credit hours taught by each category of faculty.  For example the number of student credit hours taught by Full-Time  Faculty.

name: Salary and benefits for Part-Time Faculty
description: Salary and benefits for Part-Time  Faculty or Adjuncts at your institution whose primary job is instruction.

name: Number of Part-Time Instructional Faculty
description: Number of Part-Time  Instructional Faculty or Adjuncts  at the end of the fall term.

name: Number of Student Credit Hours Taught by Part-Time Instructional Faculty
description: Indicate the number of student credit hours taught by each category of faculty.  For example the number of student credit hours taught by Part-Time / Adjunct  Faculty.

name: Salaries and Benefits for Executive Staff
description: Salary and benefits for employees who directly support the instructional function such as administrators, professionals and any other personnel whose salaries and wages are paid from a discipline's instructional budget.

name: Number of Executive Staff
description: Number of administrative and support staff including full-time staff and adding one-third of the number of part-time staff  at the end of the fall term.

name: Salaries and Benefits for Clerical and Other Professional Staff
description: Salary and benefits for employees who directly support the instructional function such as administrators, professionals and any other personnel whose salaries and wages are paid from a discipline's instructional budget.

name: Number of Clerical and Other Professional Staff
description: Number of administrative and support staff including full-time staff and adding one-third of the number of part-time staff  at the end of the fall term.

name: Non-Labor Operating Costs
description: Includes materials, supplies, software, computers, equipment, professional development, conferences and travel that directly support instructional activities.  Excludes facilities costs.

name: Program Development Full Time Faculty
description: Creating and planning curriculum at the program level for full time faculty.

name: Course Development Full Time Faculty
description: Creating and planning content and learning activities at the course level for full time faculty.

name: Teaching Full Time Faculty
description: Delivering course content, managing and monitoring student assignments and classroom (physical or virtual) activities for full time faculty.

name: Tutoring Full Time Faculty
description:
Formally providing supplemental academic assistance in support of regular coursework for full time faculty.
This is also included under Student Services.

name: Advising Full Time Faculty
description:
Assisting students with activities related to their educational experience including scheduling, academic support, planning and selecting curricular pathways and career development for full time faculty.
This is also included under Student Services.

name: Academic Service Full Time Faculty
description: Serving on committees or task forces to support teaching and learning for full time faculty.

name: Assessment and Grading Full Time Faculty
description: Assessing prior and current learning; developing and selecting assessment methodologies; evaluating student assignments and performance to award course credit, and contributing to broader assessment of student learning outcomes for full time faculty.

name: Professional Development Full Time Faculty
description: Includes institution activities and events, continuing education, community service, professional development activities, reading subject matter literature, writing scholarly papers, travel, professional association participation and other similar activities.

name: Program Development Part Time Faculty
description: Creating and planning curriculum at the program level for part time faculty.

name: Course Development Part Time Faculty
description: Creating and planning content and learning activities at the course level for part time faculty.

name: Teaching Part Time Faculty
description: Delivering course content, managing and monitoring student assignments and classroom (physical or virtual) activities for part time faculty.

name: Tutoring Part Time Faculty
description:
Formally providing supplemental academic assistance in support of regular coursework for part time faculty.
This is also included under Student Services.

name: Advising Part Time Faculty
description:

description: Assessing prior and current learning; developing and selecting assessment methodologies; evaluating student assignments and performance to award course credit, and contributing to broader assessment of student learning outcomes for part time faculty.

name: Professional Development Part Time Faculty
description: Includes institution activities and events, continuing education, community service, professional development activities, reading subject matter literature, writing scholarly papers, travel, professional association participation and other similar activities.

name: Student Credit Hours Taught by Full-Time Faculty
description: Number of student credit hours taught by full-time faculty.

name: Student Credit Hours Taught by Part-Time Faculty
description: Number of student credit hours taught by part-time faculty

description: Providing support and access to information resources in printed and electronic formats to support academic activities.

description: Providing instructional technology infrastructure and services to faculty and students. For example in-class technical assistance, training on how to use the learning management system and other new classroom technologies.

name: IPEDS Fall Enrollment
description: Full-time Credit Headcount plus Part-time Credit Headcount should equal IPEDS Enrollment.

name: Full-time Credit Headcount
description: Fall unduplicated credit enrollment

name: High School Student Concurrent Enrollment Headcount
description: High School Student Concurrent Enrollment - Headcount should be the percent of IPEDS Fall Headcount Enrollment that includes high school students enrolled either on campus, at their high school, or online.

name: High School Student Concurrent Enrollment - Credit Hours
description: High School Student Concurrent Enrollment - Credit Hours should be the percent of IPEDS Fall Credit Hour Enrollment that includes high school students enrolled either on campus, at their high school, or online.

name: Pell Grant Recipients
description: Pell Grant Recipients should be the percent of IPEDS Fall Headcount Enrollment who received Pell Grants.

name: First-generation Students
description: First-generation Students should be the percent of fall credit students that represent the first generation of their families to attend a higher education institution.

name: Transfer Credit Hours
description: Transfer Credit Hours should be the percent of IPEDS Fall Enrollment credit hours that includes full- and part-time students enrolled in courses that do not award career or technical certification, but do award credit that is transferable to other postsecondary institutions.(For example, English, History, and Math would be considered transfer credit hours.)

name: Technical/Career Credit Hours
description: Technical/Career Credit Hours should be the percent of IPEDS Fall Enrollment that includes credit hours by full- and part-time students enrolled in programs that award career or technical certification that is not transferable. (For example, automotive technology credit hours, interior design credit hours, and practical nursing credit hours would be considered technical/career credit hours.)

name: Developmental Credit Hours
description: Developmental Credit Hours should be the percent of IPEDS Fall Enrollment that includes credit hours by full- and part-time students enrolled in developmental/remedial courses as defined by the institution.

name: Credit Student Median Age
description: Use number from most recent IPEDS enrollment data.

name: Native Hawaiian or other Pacific Islander
Tuition and Fees per Credit Hour
description: Tuition and Fees per Credit Hour are the tuition and fees that full-time, in-district students are charged per credit hour. Use the figure reported to IPEDS. Enter per credit hour figure, not total tuition and fees. Credit Courses are courses that are eligible for Title IV federal financial aid.

name: Unrestricted Operating Revenue
description:
Use fiscal year 2012-2013 data.

Unrestricted Operating Revenue is defined by the National Association of College and University Business Officers (NACUBO) as "resources received that have no limitations or stipulations placed on them by external agencies or donors."

name: Local
description: Local tax revenue sources.

name: Credit Hours Taught by Full Time
description: Percentage of teaching load taught by full-time instructional faculty. Teaching load is measured by number credit hours assigned to credit sections with six or more students taught by full-time faculty at the end of the reporting term divided by the total number of student credit hours taught.  (Ex.  teaching load for a faculty member teaching 5 three-credit-hour courses would be 15 credit hours. )

name: Total Full-time Credit Hours
description: Number of credit hours taught by full-time instructional faculty where teaching load is measured by number of credit hours assigned to credit sections with six or more students taught by full-time faculty at the end of the reporting term.

name: Credit Hours Taught by Part Time
description: Percentage of teaching load taught by part-time instructional faculty. Teaching load is measured by number credit hours assigned to credit sections with six or more students taught by part-time faculty at the end of the reporting term divided by the total number of student credit hours taught.  (Ex.  teaching load for a faculty member teaching 5 three-credit-hour courses would be 15 credit hours.)

name: Total Part Time Credit Hours
description: Number of credit hours taught by part-time instructional faculty where teaching load is measured by number of credit hours assigned to credit sections with six or more students taught by full-time faculty at the end of the reporting term.

name: Credit Hours of Online Instruction
description: Courses belong in this category if all of the instruction is provided online and no face-to-face classroom instruction is required.

name: Credit Hours of Face to Face Instruction
description: Courses belong in this category when all of the instruction is provided in an in person physical classroom space.

name: Credit Hours of Hybrid Instruction
description: Courses that blend online and face-to-face delivery and typically have a reduced number of face to face meetings.

name: Instruction
description:
The amount of instruction expenses of the colleges, schools, departments, and other instructional divisions of the institution and expenses for departmental research and public service that are not separately budgeted.

The instruction category includes general academic instruction, occupational and vocational instruction, special session instruction, community education, preparatory and adult basic education, and remedial and tutorial instruction conducted by the teaching faculty for the institutionï¿_s students.

Include expenses for both credit and noncredit activities.

Exclude expenses for academic administration if the primary function is administration (e.g., academic deans.)

name: Student Services
description:
Expenses for admissions, registrar activities and activities whose primary purpose is to contribute to studentsï¿_ emotional and physical well-being and to their intellectual, cultural and social development outside the context of the formal instructional program.

Examples are career guidance, counseling, financial aid administration, student records, athletics, and student health services, except when operated as a self-supporting auxiliary enterprise.

name: Academic Support
description:
Expenses for support services that are an integral part of the institutionï¿_s primary mission of instruction, research, or public service and that are not charged directly to these primary programs.

Include expenses for libraries, museums, galleries, audio/visual services, academic development, academic computing support, course and curriculum development, and academic administration.

Include expenses for medical, veterinary and dental clinics if their primary purpose is to support the institutional program, that is, they are not part of a hospital.

name: Institutional Support
description:
Expenses for the day-to-day operational support of the institution.

Include expenses for general administrative services, executive direction and planning, legal and fiscal operations, administrative computing support, and public relations/development.

name: Research
description:
Expenses for activities specifically organized to produce research outcomes and either commissioned by an agency external to the institution or separately budgeted by an organizational unit within the institution.

The category includes institutes and research centers, and individual and project research.

Do not report non-research sponsored programs (e.g., training programs) on this line.

name: Public service
description:
Expenses specifically for public service and for activities established primarily to provide non-instructional services beneficial to groups external to the institution.

Examples are seminars and projects provided to the particular sectors of the community.

Include expenses for community services, cooperative extension services, and public broadcasting services.

name: Operation and maintenance
description:
Expenses for operations established to provide service and maintenance related to campus grounds and facilities used for educational and general purposes.

Specific expenses include utilities, fire protection, property insurance, and similar items. This function does not include amounts charged to auxiliary enterprises, hospitals, and independent operations.

Also includes information technology expenses related to operation and maintenance of plant activities if the institution separately budgets and expenses information technology resources (otherwise these expenses are included in institutional support).

Institutions may, as an option, distribute depreciation expense to this function.

Operation and maintenance represents the sum of operation and maintenance expenses allocated to each of the following functional expenses: instruction, student services, academic support, institutional support, research, and public service
